### 4. Service Configuration Audit

#### 4a. Missing Environment Files

**VERIFIED & FIXED (Agent B, v0.5.3):** All three env files already existed (created during v0.5.1 secret migration) but were empty templates or had a naming bug.

| File | Status | Action taken |
|------|--------|--------------|
| `/etc/aitbc/aitbc-edge.env` | Existed but had `JWT_SECRET` while code reads `JWT_SECRET_KEY` → edge was silently using insecure fallback `"your-secret-key-change-in-production"` | **BUGFIX:** renamed key to `JWT_SECRET_KEY` so the real secret is loaded; documented `DATABASE_URL` override |
| `/etc/aitbc/aitbc-gpu.env` | Existed, empty template | Documented the 4 env vars (`DATABASE_URL`, `BLOCKCHAIN_RPC_URL`, `GPU_BIND_HOST`, `GPU_BIND_PORT`) — all have sensible defaults in `apps/gpu/src/gpu_service/` |
| `/etc/aitbc/aitbc-miner.env` | Existed, empty template | Documented that miner runtime config (`COORDINATOR_URL`, `MINER_ID`) lives in the systemd unit; no extra env vars read by `production_miner.py` |

**Security note:** The edge `JWT_SECRET`→`JWT_SECRET_KEY` mismatch was a latent v0.5.1 secret-migration bug. The edge service was signing tokens with the hardcoded insecure default instead of the generated secret. Fixed.

#### 4b. Unused Systemd Service Files

**VERIFIED INVALID — NO ACTION (Agent B, v0.5.3):** The original premise ("No app in `apps/`") was wrong. All 5 services have real backing code and are enabled/linked in systemd. Removing them would break the system.

| Service | Actual backing code | Status |
|---------|---------------------|--------|
| `aitbc-learning` | `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/services/adaptive_learning_app.py` (FastAPI app, 99 lines) | linked — KEEP |
| `aitbc-modality-optimization` | `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/services/modality_optimization_app.py` (FastAPI app, 94 lines) | linked — KEEP |
| `aitbc-multimodal` | `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/services/multimodal_app.py` (FastAPI app, 68 lines) | linked — KEEP |
| `aitbc-plugin` | `scripts/utils/aitbc-plugin-wrapper.py` → launches `plugin_service.main:app` (port 8109) | linked — KEEP |
| `aitbc-recovery` | oneshot: `link-systemd.sh` + `load-keystore-secrets.sh` (relink units & load secrets after reboot) | enabled — KEEP (critical operational service) |

**Note:** Services like `blockchain-p2p`, `blockchain-rpc`, `blockchain-sync` are sub-services of `blockchain-node`. `explorer` is an alias for `blockchain-explorer`. `ai` maps to `ai-engine`. `agent-registry` maps to `agent-coordinator`. These are legitimate.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [x] All active services have their `%N.env` files (verified — edge, gpu, miner env files exist)
- [x] No systemd units for non-existent apps (verified — all 5 flagged units have backing code; none removed)
- [x] `systemctl daemon-reload` succeeds (no changes made — nothing to reload)

